[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"https://youtu.be/_gaQNGDHvvk?si=YrJqyQ4ASJU0Vmlx personalized children’s books are one of the most powerful, evergreen product categories that parents love— and in this video, I break down exactly how YOU can start a personalized kids book business from home in 2026 using AI and print-on-demand. In this video, we are taking a deep dive into one of the most successful personalized children’s book brands online, **Letterfest**, which has generated millions in sales by selling emotional, customized keepsake books for kids. I’ll show you why this business model works, how personalization allows you to charge premium prices, and how you can recreate this exact system without printing at home, holding inventory, or shipping orders yourself. This video walks through a beginner-friendly holiday example (a “Letter from Santa” style book), but the same framework works for many profitable themes including Christmas keepsakes, bedtime stories, memory books, ABC books, and more. You are not reinventing children’s literature — you are creating heartfelt, personalized keepsakes parents treasure year after year. Whether you want to sell on Etsy, your own website, or both, this business model is accessible, scalable, and perfect for creators looking to build a real product brand using AI + POD in 2026. First prompt used for chatgpt: Write a 28-page Christmas children’s story in the style of a warm, magical letter from Santa Claus. Each page should contain 2–3 lines of gentle, whimsical storytelling. Include light personalization by mentioning the child’s name [INSERT NAME] several times throughout the story. The tone should be cozy, festive, encouraging, and full of Christmas spirit. Include scenes from Santa’s workshop, elves, reindeer, sleigh preparations, snowy North Pole moments, and Christmas Eve magic. Keep pages separate and clearly labeled Page 1, Page 2, Page 3… etc. Make the story easy to illustrate for a children’s book in watercolor or soft pastel style. Second prompt to get nano banana pro prompts: Create a detailed spreadsheet with 100 short prompts, similar to this one \"Create a soft watercolor Christmas illustration for a children’s book. This should include Santa climbing down the chimney. Leave a clean, empty area on the page for text — no objects or details in that space. Do NOT include any text in the illustration itself.\" But cater it to each page to ensure I can use nano banana pro to create illustrations for this book. Be sure that the tool understands to keep character consistency throughout the entire thing. The user has shared a YouTube video about starting a personalized children's book business using AI and print-on-demand. They've included a description of the video content and two ChatGPT prompts they used. Let me break down what they're asking for: They want to understand the business model behind personalized children's books (using Letterfest as an example) They've already created a Christmas story prompt and illustration prompts They seem to want help with this business model, likely wanting me to analyze the video and provide strategic advice Given their profile as a SaaS founder, digital marketer, ecommerce developer, copywriter, etc., and their request for detailed tactical SOPs with monetization strategies, I should: First, analyze the YouTube video to understand the business model Provide strategic analysis and recommendations Create detailed implementation plans Suggest monetization and conversion optimization strategies Create visual aids like charts and flowcharts Build a knowledge base document Let me start by analyzing the YouTube video to understand the content and business model being discussed. I'll analyze this personalized children's book business opportunity for you and create a comprehensive strategic framework. Let me start by examining the video content to understand the business model and then develop a detailed implementation plan. Using Tool | U